
                  $VER: BumpRev_Documentation 47.1 (06.02.2022)
                  =============================================

BumpRev is a program to generate version/revision strings for C and assembly
language, which can be included into programmer's source files. These 
strings are written in the standard AmigaDOS version information format, 
so they will allow users to determine version/revision of the binaries via
the AmigaDOS "version" command. 

Bumprev may be especially useful to handle "revision bumping" automatically
via makefiles. 

Invoking BumpRev
----------------

BumpRev can only by run from the Shell like this:

  Bumprev <version> <revname>  
  
  Example:
  
      bumprev 49 my_program
      
      will bump the revision of the program "my_program" by one. If no 
      revision files exist in the curreent path, bumprev will create
      them with the initial version/revision "49.1".
      
      The following files will be created/updated by bumprev:
      
          myprogram_rev.h:
          ----------------
              #define VERSION         49
              #define REVISION        1
              #define DATE            "6.2.2022"
              #define VERS            "myprogram 49.1"
              #define VSTRING         "myprogram 49.1 (6.2.2022)\r\n"
              #define VERSTAG         "\0$VER: myprogram 49.1 (6.2.2022)"

          myprogram_rev.i:
          ----------------
              VERSION         EQU     49
              REVISION        EQU     1

              DATE    MACRO
                              dc.b '6.2.2022'
                              ENDM

              VERS    MACRO
                              dc.b 'myprogram 49.1'
                              ENDM

              VSTRING MACRO
                              dc.b 'myprogram 49.1 (6.2.2022)',13,10,0
                              ENDM

              VERSTAG MACRO
                              dc.b 0,'$VER: myprogram 49.1 (6.2.2022)',0
                              ENDM
                              
               
          myprogram_rev.rev:
          ------------------
              used by BumpRev to store the current revision 
              ("1" in this case)
          
      